{{- if or .Pairings .Resolutions -}}
{{- if .Pairings -}}
FlavorGraph pairing suggestions for the current ingredients (contested
compound-sharing signal — see the system prompt). Cite one as
{source: "flavorgraph", ref: "pairing:<ingredient>", date: ""}:
{{range .Pairings}}- {{.Ingredient}} (score {{printf "%.2f" .Score}})
{{end}}{{- end -}}
{{- if .Resolutions}}
Resolved ingredient entities (deterministic USDA FoodData Central / FoodOn
resolution). Cite one as {source: "usda-fdc", ref: "fdc:<fdc_id>", date: ""}
or {source: "foodon", ref: "<foodon_id>", date: ""}:
{{range .Resolutions}}- {{.Canonical}}: fdc_id={{orNull .FDCID}}, foodon_id={{orNull .FoodOnID}}
{{end}}{{- end -}}
{{- if or .Pairings .Resolutions}}
When a flavor_rationale claim rests on this evidence, its provenance field
takes the bare ref string (e.g. "pairing:basil", "fdc:171077",
"foodon:FOODON_03411343").
{{- end -}}
{{- else -}}
No grounding evidence is supplied for this run. Cite nothing: every flavor
claim must carry a null provenance and be listed in unverified.
{{- end -}}
